  "text": "The event handler chain flows through 6 core files in client-go/tools/cache: (1) listwatch.go defines ListerWatcher interface and ListWatch struct that perform List+Watch against the API server; (2) reflector.go's Reflector uses a ListerWatcher to watch the API server and pushes events into a Store (the DeltaFIFO); (3) delta_fifo.go implements DeltaFIFO, a producer-consumer queue that accumulates Deltas (Added/Updated/Deleted/Replaced/Sync) per object key; (4) controller.go's processDeltas() pops Deltas from the DeltaFIFO, updates the cache Store (indexer), and invokes OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete on the ResourceEventHandler; (5) shared_informer.go's sharedIndexInformer.HandleDeltas calls processDeltas with itself as the handler, and its OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete methods call sharedProcessor.distribute() to fan out notifications to all registered processorListeners; (6) store.go defines the Store interface and the cache struct that serves as the thread-safe in-memory object store (indexer) updated during processDeltas.",
